Description: Fragment of oval, tapering handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Production date: 139 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Pencil '2.3', worn, circled. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 128, 1. Name Lapheides. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0168.05.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1008)
Additional IDs: Miscellaneous number: Pencil '731 and worn, circled
